==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: melamine-fromaldehyde methanal resin
<hw>melamine-fromaldehyde methanal resin</hw>
<pos>n.</pos> <def>A thermosetting plastic formed by the reaction of
melamine and formaldehyde. It is used for molding and for preparing
laminated sheets used to surface counter tops, walls, and furniture. The
commercially marketed <styp><er>Formica</er></styp> (TM) is one type of
melamine resin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melampode</ent>⟦br⟧
